  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/tutorial/FunctionalOperations.\
html#17469"], None},
  ButtonNote->
   "https://reference.wolfram.com/language/tutorial/FunctionalOperations.html#\
17469"],
 ", indicated in their most common form by ending with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "&"], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b816c0e7-73fa-4242-9f40-cbbe6e3ff4ff"],
 ". The argument to the function is indicated by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "#"], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"4cf03f6f-3b9d-45c8-932c-265fa4896699"],
 " (multiple arguments can be indicated using ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "#1"], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"9160942e-8080-4000-b4f1-5e02897ecfd5"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "#2"], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"a7c4eeff-d237-47ca-aa44-5a5dacf364a9"],
 " and so on)."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f987381d-ac83-4d61-bef1-f5aba9ced034"],

Cell["You can define a function to do the following:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"07a54f48-be87-4fc9-95cc-4895cc81e292"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"myFunction", "[", "x_", "]"}], ":=", 
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
   RowBox[{"3", "x"}], "-", "2"}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"1dd279b4-6a1f-\
4bc5-9d7a-2f948f5c9a0f"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"myFunction", "[", "2", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[41]:=",ExpressionUUID->"5c004bbe-f588-4eba-ad80-6b180cbf9661"],

Cell[BoxData["8"], "Output",
 CellLabel->"Out[41]=",ExpressionUUID->"6162f2b0-45a2-4b86-9f1c-df44f0a56769"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["Or you can do this with a pure function:", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"a9722d6b-1a2c-457a-a18f-7cffe599cca6"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["#", "2"], "+", 
   RowBox[{"3", "#"}], "-", "2"}], "&"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"32432d90-\
9aef-45e2-a0bb-9df05c78fa7d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Function", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["#", "2"], "+", 
   RowBox[{"3", "#"}], "-", "2"}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"0a234eab-\
2097-4654-afc2-7d1b2a62dfef"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Function", "[", 
  RowBox[{"x", ",", 
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["x", "2"], "+", 
    RowBox[{"3", "x"}], "-", "2"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->\
"d825919e-0df3-40f4-ab75-be953b19be55"],

Cell["\<\
Pure functions allow you to give functions that can be applied to arguments \
without having to define explicit names for either the functions or arguments.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"eaf6d9f6-4981-4806-a6f6-07ce157661f6"],

Cell["A pure function can be used on one input:", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"9c35a230-6525-4ef4-9c31-8f6cd5b52fbe"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["#", "2"], "+", 
    RowBox[{"3", "#"}], "-", "2"}], "&"}], "[", "42", "]"}]], "Input",Expressi\
onUUID->"a10d2370-b40a-497f-a436-fb446a2c9029"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Or it can be used on (say) a list of inputs using ",
 ButtonBox["Map",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Map.html"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Map.html"],
 ":"
}], "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"a5e55034-3f3e-40c7-a88a-b7a07552b84f"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["#", "2"], "+", 
    RowBox[{"3", "#"}], "-", "2"}], "&"}], "/@", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"23", ",", "42", ",", "56"}], "}"}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->\
"59e20be6-5f0c-4b66-bfae-1de8d79235f6"],

Cell["This pure function takes more than one argument:", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"1246f704-7d37-41af-b73b-e0fb47c1bafe"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"#1", "+", 
    RowBox[{"2", " ", "#2"}], "+", 
    RowBox[{"#3", "^", "3"}]}], "&"}], "[", 
  RowBox[{"a", ",", "b", ",", "c"}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->\
"d285360b-5065-4650-be0b-9f829c3b801d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "If you are going to use a particular function repeatedly, then you probably \
should define the function using ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"f", "[", "x_", "]"}], ":=", "body"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->
  "ae0845c1-3f78-4aeb-8eb2-e28254242d0f"],
 " and refer to it by its name. On the other hand, if you only intend to use \
a function once, you will likely find it better to write the function in its \
\"pure\" form without ever naming it or its dummy variables."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"07738d23-31c4-43b6-b1c4-81e05300b7a1"],

Cell["Pure functions have many advantages:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"aec8054e-2a8d-4497-a55b-3f66a59774fc"],

Cell["Allow for more compact code", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"1b7e17a4-91bc-49e2-b606-86faf8be8dbb"],

Cell["Keep namespace clear", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"152e9070-0e9b-4241-83f5-870f71c46f69"],

Cell["Do not need to scope variables", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"63c630fb-c9a1-4034-8309-ba85f3fe45dc"],

Cell["Will auto-compile where possible", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"c5320e77-ec27-429e-9740-41af2dcdea22"],

Cell["\<\
The cumulative effect of these advantages is that pure functions will often \
run faster than their siblings based on DownValues.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9b2cd40e-15c4-4448-abc8-0b92171cf091"],

Cell["Pure functions do have a few disadvantages, however:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"71b320ce-b43d-4e65-a7a7-890455c7ce4a"],

Cell["\<\
May be more difficult to read, especially for people who are not the author\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"2a7328f5-37c9-479e-a0bc-d1438e3ea6fd"],

Cell["Can be difficult to nest with multiple variables", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"926de113-a883-4dd9-b70c-353d0df99d28"],

Cell["\<\
Do not include some of the useful pattern-matching constructs of named \
functions\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"353790c0-68db-4d60-bcc2-20536b1037b3"],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
 DynamicModuleBox[{WolframUTools`Private`cyuOpen$$ = False}, 
  DynamicBox[ToBoxes[
    Grid[
     Join[{{
        Button[
         Mouseover[
          TextCell[
           Framed[
            Style["Check Your Understanding", "CYUButton"], RoundingRadius -> 
            5, FrameMargins -> {{18, 18}, {15, 15}}, ImageSize -> Automatic, 
            BaseStyle -> "Text"], "CYUButton"], 
          TextCell[
           Framed[
            Style["Check Your Understanding", "CYUButton"], RoundingRadius -> 
            5, FrameMargins -> {{18, 18}, {15, 15}}, ImageSize -> Automatic, 
            BaseStyle -> "Text"], "CYUButtonActive"]], (
         WolframUTools`Private`cyuOpen$$ = 
         Not[WolframUTools`Private`cyuOpen$$])& , Appearance -> None, 
         Evaluator -> Automatic, Method -> "Preemptive"]}}, 
      If[WolframUTools`Private`cyuOpen$$, {{
         Framed[
          Column[{
            TextCell[
            "Which of the following defines a pure function that takes \
multiple inputs?", "Text"], 
            DynamicModule[{WolframUTools`Private`qState = None}, 
             RadioButtonBar[
              Dynamic[WolframUTools`Private`qState], {1 -> Dynamic[
                 Column[
                  If[WolframUTools`Private`qState === 1, {
                    TextCell[
                    "#[[1]] + #[[2]] &", "Text", FontColor -> RGBColor[
                    Rational[4, 9], 0, 0], FontWeight -> Bold], 
                    TextCell[
                    "Incorrect: This defines a pure function with only one \
input\[LongDash]but the pure function will access the first and second parts \
of that input.", "Text", FontColor -> RGBColor[
                    Rational[2, 3], 0, 0]]}, {
                    TextCell["#[[1]] + #[[2]] &", "Text"]}], 
                  BaselinePosition -> {1, 1}, Spacings -> 0]], 2 -> Dynamic[
                 Column[
                  If[WolframUTools`Private`qState === 2, {
                    TextCell["#[1] + #[2] &", "Text", FontColor -> RGBColor[
                    Rational[4, 9], 0, 0], FontWeight -> Bold], 
                    TextCell[
                    "Incorrect: This defines a pure function where the input \
will be used as a function that takes 1 and 2 as inputs.", "Text", FontColor -> 
                    RGBColor[
                    Rational[2, 3], 0, 0]]}, {
                    TextCell["#[1] + #[2] &", "Text"]}], 
                  BaselinePosition -> {1, 1}, Spacings -> 0]], 3 -> Dynamic[
                 Column[
                  If[WolframUTools`Private`qState === 3, {
                    TextCell["#1 + #2 &", "Text", FontColor -> RGBColor[0, 
                    Rational[4, 9], 0], FontWeight -> Bold], 
                    TextCell[
                    "Correct: A pure function that takes one input can use # \
to represent that input, but # is shorthand for #1. When more inputs are \
required, the number after the # represents the index of the inputs.", "Text",
                     FontColor -> RGBColor[0, 
                    Rational[2, 3], 0]]}, {
                    TextCell["#1 + #2 &", "Text"]}], 
                  BaselinePosition -> {1, 1}, Spacings -> 0]], 4 -> Dynamic[
                 Column[
                  If[WolframUTools`Private`qState === 4, {
                    TextCell["#_1 + #_2 &", "Text", FontColor -> RGBColor[
                    Rational[4, 9], 0, 0], FontWeight -> Bold], 
                    TextCell[
                    "Incorrect: This is a syntax nightmare; trying to use \
subscripts should generally be avoided and certainly in a context like this, \
where the underscore is interpreted as a Blank.", "Text", FontColor -> 
                    RGBColor[
                    Rational[2, 3], 0, 0]]}, {
                    TextCell["#_1 + #_2 &", "Text"]}], 
                  BaselinePosition -> {1, 1}, Spacings -> 0]]}, Appearance -> 
              "Vertical", BaselinePosition -> Automatic], 
             DynamicModuleValues :> {}]}], FrameStyle -> Directive[
            GrayLevel[0.92], 
            Thickness[Large]], RoundingRadius -> 0, Background -> 
          GrayLevel[0.97], FrameMargins -> 15]}}, {}]], Spacings -> 2, 
     Alignment -> {Left, Baseline}, ItemSize -> Scaled[1], BaseStyle -> 
     "Text"], StandardForm],
   ImageSizeCache->{1005., {22.574980042874813`, 29.807401917874813`}}],
  DynamicModuleValues:>{}]],ExpressionUUID->"fa46434f-178f-4eae-bfa7-\
6de025223554"]], "Text",
 CellTags->"CYU",ExpressionUUID->"e4461b4d-ba84-436d-9bc1-adf61b24b010"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Tips for Efficient Coding", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"00dad0f3-e2ee-459f-a3ec-3f51aac6fcd8"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Avoid Appending", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"ec312d03-8e17-4a67-b6d5-84d569d3bfeb"],

Cell["Consider a simple list:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"63968524-53f5-401e-b8e2-86d0691c0182"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"list", "=", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"1", ",", "2", ",", "3", ",", "4", ",", "5"}], "}"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[245]:=",ExpressionUUID->"5d80eded-ae9f-4c89-a1f1-161218dcd5d2"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"1", ",", "2", ",", "3", ",", "4", ",", "5"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[245]=",ExpressionUUID->"03563434-e582-44fa-b47b-0bbe1cb5cd29"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "You can permanently modify ",
 StyleBox["list", "Input"],
 " by using functions like ",
 ButtonBox["AppendTo",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/AppendTo.html"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/AppendTo.html"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d737ed5c-58dd-4e7a-aec5-b2225a09ecb4"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"AppendTo", "[", 
  RowBox[{"list", ",", "6"}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[246]:=",ExpressionUUID->"d9759c12-2bf6-4bee-8a2d-d27e2eb51786"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"1", ",", "2", ",", "3", ",", "4", ",", "5", ",", "6"}], 
  "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[246]=",ExpressionUUID->"1e5c2b0f-1d81-422b-9399-fcd95f0418eb"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData["list"], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[247]:=",ExpressionUUID->"aa4a6633-76f2-47f7-990f-2e43741d95a4"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"1", ",", "2", ",", "3", ",", "4", ",", "5", ",", "6"}], 
  "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[247]=",ExpressionUUID->"3446cfc4-4fde-4c0e-b3d0-bf5a62f05103"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
Because of the flexibility of Wolfram Language data structures, AppendTo \
cannot assume that you will be appending a number\[LongDash]after all, you \
might be appending a document or a sound or an image. As a result, AppendTo \
must create a fresh copy of the data that has been restructured to \
accommodate the appended information. (In other words: AppendTo unpacks \
arrays.)\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6e3b0a3f-a873-4857-a4c5-be09b0f9ee1a"],

Cell["This makes it progressively slower as the data accumulates:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e283f245-f287-4fcf-bbee-b92020055a68"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"data", "=", 
    RowBox[{"{", "}"}]}], ";", 
   RowBox[{"Do", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"AppendTo", "[", 
      RowBox[{"data", ",", 
       RowBox[{"RandomReal", "[", "x", "]"}]}], "]"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "40000"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], ";"}], "//", 
  "AbsoluteTiming"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[248]:=",ExpressionUUID->"d66cab3b-f765-4574-8374-99d22d97c56a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"7.0767098`", ",", "Null"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[248]=",ExpressionUUID->"ea091171-884e-433d-a609-6a1cf2ef1b37"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Instead, use alternatives like ",
 ButtonBox["Sow",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Sow.html"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Sow.html"],
 " and ",
 ButtonBox["Reap",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Reap.html"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Reap.html"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"86325fef-3205-4bd7-9211-b84a6b06b54c"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"data", "=", 
    RowBox[{"{", "}"}]}], ";", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"Reap", "[", 
     RowBox[{"Do", "[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"Sow", "[", 
        RowBox[{"data", ",", 
         RowBox[{"RandomReal", "[", "x", "]"}]}], "]"}], ",", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"x", ",", "0", ",", "40000"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "]"}], "[", 
    RowBox[{"[", "2", "]"}], "]"}], ";"}], "//", "AbsoluteTiming"}]], "Input",\

 CellTags->{"Reap", "Sow"},
 CellLabel->
  "In[249]:=",ExpressionUUID->"f09f9e5e-e1f6-40a0-9726-6a8eeb1dec1f"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0.837438`", ",", "Null"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellTags->{"Reap", "Sow"},
 CellLabel->
  "Out[249]=",ExpressionUUID->"9b43b7e5-fe74-43dd-8c93-749541bc0595"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Keep DRY", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"8d6a93db-c73c-4198-97d7-11f06d8b2fe1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Do not repeat yourself (DRY, or sometimes do not repeat yourself) is ",
 ButtonBox["a principle of software development",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Don%27t_repeat_yourself"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Don%27t_repeat_yourself"],
 " aimed at reducing repetition of software patterns."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d9057d5c-3031-4dc5-99b7-9f4e44af4d00"],

Cell["\<\
Violations of DRY are typically referred to as WET solutions, which is \
commonly taken to stand for either \"write everything twice,\" \"we enjoy \
typing\" or \"waste everyone's time.\"\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"50a63172-d74e-4c19-8270-f07db57e7709"],

Cell["\<\
Suppose that you have several APIs that you need to access with corresponding \
usernames and email addresses.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9c4846e9-db10-4c5a-9a02-3a3354087835"],

Cell["Do not do this:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"99abe2e3-9425-4d61-a6bd-f4847bb83367"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"(*", 
   RowBox[{"flow", " ", "1"}], "*)"}], "\n", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"username1", "=", "yourUsernameHere"}], ";"}], "\n", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"email1", "=", "yourEmailAddressHere"}], ";"}], "\n", 
   RowBox[{"URLRead", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<http://myapi1.com\>\"", ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"\"\<username\>\"", "\[Rule]", "username1"}], ",", 
       RowBox[{"\"\<email\>\"", "\[Rule]", "email1"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "\n",
    "\n", 
   RowBox[{"(*", 
    RowBox[{"flow", " ", "2"}], "*)"}], "\n", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"username2", "=", "yourUsernameHere"}], ";"}], "\n", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"email2", "=", "yourEmailAddressHere"}], ";"}], "\n", 
   RowBox[{"URLRead", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<http://myapi2.com\>\"", ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"\"\<username\>\"", "\[Rule]", "username2"}], ",", 
       RowBox[{"\"\<email\>\"", "\[Rule]", "email2"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}], 
   "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
   RowBox[{"(*", 
    RowBox[{"flow", " ", "3"}], "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"username3", "=."}], ".."}]}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->\
"a7cb4bfa-79a1-4a48-922c-baad77e01920"],

Cell["Do this instead:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"db19bbee-4a7f-4d6e-867c-4204e86b6b11"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"(*", "flow", "*)"}], "\n", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"doAPIRequest", "[", 
     RowBox[{"url_", ",", "username_", ",", "email_"}], "]"}], " ", ":=", 
    "\n", "\t", 
    RowBox[{"URLRead", "[", 
     RowBox[{"url", ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"\"\<username\>\"", "\[Rule]", "username"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"\"\<email\>\"", "\[Rule]", "email"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], 
   "\n", "\n", 
   RowBox[{"doAPIRequest", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<http://myapi1.com\>\"", ",", "username1", ",", "email1"}], 
    "]"}], "\n", "\n", 
   RowBox[{"doAPIRequest", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<http://myapi2.com\>\"", ",", "username2", ",", "email2"}], 
    "]"}]}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"902ebe89-dae3-4a34-9dcf-\
cc11eefcd7b7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Depending on your particular needs, you may want to go further by taking \
advantage of \"structure-based\" functions like ",
 ButtonBox["MapThread",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/MapThread.html"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/MapThread.html"],
 " or even ",
 ButtonBox["MapApply",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/MapApply.html"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/MapApply.html"],
 " (@@@) with pure anonymous functions:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"02ad789e-4052-4110-bb88-047219af35f1"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"MapThread", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"URLRead", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\"\<http://my\>\"", "<>", "#1", "<>", "\"\<.com\>\""}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"\"\<username\>\"", "->", "#2"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"\"\<email\>\"", "->", "#3"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "&"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<api1\>\"", ",", "\"\<user1\>\"", ",", "\"\<email1\>\""}], 
      "}"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<api2\>\"", ",", "\"\<user2\>\"", ",", "\"\<email2\>\""}], 
      "}"}], ",", "..."}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"915ed8be-\
3ad1-42a5-a39a-2ed931e5dbdf"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"URLRead", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"\"\<http://\>\"", "<>", "#1", "<>", "\"\<.com\>\""}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"\"\<username\>\"", "->", "#2"}], ",", 
       RowBox[{"\"\<email\>\"", "->", "#3"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}], "&"}], "@@@", 
  
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<api1\>\"", ",", "\"\<user1\>\"", ",", "\"\<email1\>\""}], 
     "}"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<api2\>\"", ",", "\"\<user2\>\"", ",", "\"\<email2\>\""}], 
     "}"}], ",", "..."}], "}"}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"d0fb99c3-6a10-\
47b4-ad4c-1d6230b06405"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Stay Functional", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"3e0d03f5-0de3-4659-a5ca-1801cb9a25ea"],

Cell["\<\
If you tend to think procedurally out of habit, it is worth trying to change \
that habit.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"225f6bc3-9d3d-4c63-adbb-bf716a9d4ef1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Consider taking the product of the first ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["2", "16"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b8b9c53e-48b7-4825-bf94-835434f3444d"],
 " integers."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"69c611ae-8395-42aa-90de-d06ce1b6cfcc"],

Cell["Procedurally, that might look like:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"92065a2d-2547-46f9-9a81-4c9330ea7e56"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"RepeatedTiming", "[", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"temp", "=", "1"}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
   RowBox[{"Do", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"temp", "*=", "i"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"i", ",", "1", ",", 
       RowBox[{"2", "^", "16"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]",
    "temp", ";"}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[207]:=",ExpressionUUID->"747c65cc-bbd7-4aad-8e49-d9bdd47f808a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0.30749875`", ",", "Null"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[207]=",ExpressionUUID->"5874386c-eadd-4ea0-b9fd-bbee6f219385"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Functionally, you can think of this as converting the list of these \
integers directly into a product with ",
 ButtonBox["Apply",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Apply.html"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Apply.html"],
 " (@@):"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e6a23528-9167-4b9b-841a-8db684a9a29c"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"RepeatedTiming", "[", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Times", "@@", 
    RowBox[{"Range", "[", 
     RowBox[{"2", "^", "16"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[208]:=",ExpressionUUID->"d76aaa2f-3551-4d95-9060-ebf69a85adb9"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0.052781`", ",", "Null"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[208]=",ExpressionUUID->"7afa9a0c-1652-40b7-acfc-4135c285759f"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Use Built-in Functions", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"447bc364-82fa-40f0-a65e-2a578bf490d5"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Norm", "Subsubsection",ExpressionUUID->"6ed3b7f1-59bd-40bb-a667-eb3e39b70bb7"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"pts", "=", 
   RowBox[{"RandomInteger", "[", 
    RowBox[{"10", ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"10", "^", "5"}], ",", "2"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}]], "Input",\

 CellTags->"RandomInteger",
 CellLabel->
  "In[260]:=",ExpressionUUID->"c84e4089-6bbc-4708-a44e-04301fd542a4"],

Cell["\<\
You can use a loop to compute the distances from each point in the randomly \
generated set of points to the origin:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"02436362-4599-4b50-b365-9f3cb26e3b8f"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"RepeatedTiming", "[", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"tmp", "=", 
    RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
     RowBox[{"Null", ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"Length", "[", "pts", "]"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], ";", 
   "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
   RowBox[{"Do", "[", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"tmp", "[", 
       RowBox[{"[", "k", "]"}], "]"}], "=", 
      SqrtBox[
       RowBox[{
        SuperscriptBox[
         RowBox[{"pts", "[", 
          RowBox[{"[", 
           RowBox[{"k", ",", "1"}], "]"}], "]"}], "2"], "+", 
        SuperscriptBox[
         RowBox[{"pts", "[", 
          RowBox[{"[", 
           RowBox[{"k", ",", "2"}], "]"}], "]"}], "2"]}]]}], ",", 
     "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"k", ",", "1", ",", 
       RowBox[{"Length", "[", "pts", "]"}]}], "}"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    "]"}]}], "]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"tmp", ";"}]}], "Input",
 CellTags->{"Table", "Null", "Length", "AbsoluteTiming", "Do"},
 CellLabel->
  "In[261]:=",ExpressionUUID->"055b125e-12a4-44ee-a2b0-b2aabb143def"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"20.344051`", ",", "Null"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellTags->{"Table", "Null", "Length", "AbsoluteTiming", "Do"},
 CellLabel->
  "Out[261]=",ExpressionUUID->"b93a9e25-c6bc-493a-8215-bed8b206b5ad"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "If you use the built-in function ",
 ButtonBox["Norm",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Norm.html"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Norm.html"],
 " to compute the same quantity and use Map to distribute this operation over \
all the points, the result is roughly 50 times faster:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0d776924-e01f-458d-878d-80477e2c2a46"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"RepeatedTiming", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Map", "[", 
    RowBox[{"Norm", ",", "pts"}], "]"}], ";"}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellTags->{"RepeatedTiming", "Map", "Norm"},
 CellLabel->
  "In[263]:=",ExpressionUUID->"d35b3512-ea16-417a-8e45-41923b8c062f"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0.3704155`", ",", "Null"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellTags->{"RepeatedTiming", "Map", "Norm"},
 CellLabel->
  "Out[263]=",ExpressionUUID->"256d49ba-e013-492c-ae0a-a5b3399fb667"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Sort", "Subsubsection",ExpressionUUID->"5a60f3b9-41b8-41ef-883a-bf8512f45360"],

Cell["Consider the basic computational problem of sorting numbers:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9b120cd8-f13d-42a1-b0c1-1f9dc7aed105"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"data", "=", 
   RowBox[{"RandomChoice", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Range", "[", "1000", "]"}], ",", "1000"}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}]], "Input",
 CellTags->{"RandomChoice", "Range"},
 CellLabel->
  "In[264]:=",ExpressionUUID->"e2981b2c-224d-451b-8682-e8ad9c518fc4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Here is an implementation of the selection sort algorithm that uses a loop \
that iterates over the two variables ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "i"], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"85c91524-ec04-4b4a-b49a-f6fa1f96e4dc"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "j"], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"474c407a-5a19-40a1-ae2c-7bca3268e5b7"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"469f8348-0b1d-4ec8-ba0f-c2770c01c75d"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"RepeatedTiming", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Do", "[", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"If", "[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
        "data", "\[LeftDoubleBracket]", "i", "\[RightDoubleBracket]"}], ">", 
        RowBox[{
        "data", "\[LeftDoubleBracket]", "j", "\[RightDoubleBracket]"}]}], ",", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"data", "\[LeftDoubleBracket]", 
         RowBox[{"{", 
          RowBox[{"i", ",", "j"}], "}"}], "\[RightDoubleBracket]"}], "=", 
        RowBox[{"data", "\[LeftDoubleBracket]", 
         RowBox[{"{", 
          RowBox[{"j", ",", "i"}], "}"}], "\[RightDoubleBracket]"}]}]}], 
      "]"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"i", ",", 
       RowBox[{"Length", "[", "data", "]"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"j", ",", 
       RowBox[{"i", "+", "1"}], ",", 
       RowBox[{"Length", "[", "data", "]"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}], ";"}], 
  "]"}]], "Input",
 CellTags->"If",
 CellLabel->"In[265]:=",
 CellID->1496876378,ExpressionUUID->"07b18c77-ecdf-4324-b173-5469b01d3895"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0.427766`", ",", "Null"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellTags->"If",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[265]=",ExpressionUUID->"b33a1887-9f2c-4a65-a362-4f14120997ff"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["A rule-based implementation of a bubble sort is much faster:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a834436e-ba31-4cad-9c28-60fee275412a"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"bubbleSort", " ", "=", 
  RowBox[{"RepeatedTiming", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"data", "//.", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"a___", ",", " ", "b_", ",", " ", "c_", ",", " ", "d___"}], 
        "}"}], " ", "/;", " ", 
       RowBox[{"b", " ", ">", " ", "c"}]}], " ", "->", " ", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"a", ",", " ", "c", ",", " ", "b", ",", " ", "d"}], "}"}]}]}], 
    ";"}], "]"}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"92e336b5-2a15-4c7e-970b-\
5f519dcf0d17"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0.00376271484375`", ",", "Null"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[266]=",ExpressionUUID->"9c9804f7-2258-46ed-9b52-8b18b77b5cf2"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Of course, the most efficient way to do this is just to use the built-in ",
 ButtonBox["Sort",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Sort.html"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Sort.html"],
 " function:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c6c8dd19-9953-4277-b6b0-0005fe5817d6"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"RepeatedTiming", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Sort", "[", "data", "]"}], ";"}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellTags->"Sort",
 CellLabel->
  "In[268]:=",ExpressionUUID->"0de2f99d-1b4c-46a2-abe9-5473a51e26f4"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"1.456592559814453`*^-6", ",", "Null"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellTags->"Sort",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[268]=",ExpressionUUID->"fcefbb27-3074-4e4e-a0cf-70b871374056"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Sin", "Subsubsection",ExpressionUUID->"e4ed9b7a-07ab-48d7-9f3d-43259f1bf0e8"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"pts", "=", 
   RowBox[{"RandomReal", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"0", ",", "\[Pi]"}], "}"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"10", "^", "5"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[235]:=",ExpressionUUID->"074f5a7f-0c5b-4bb3-bb03-a5f406a5f959"],

Cell["\<\
Consider taking the sines of all of these values with a procedural-style loop:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b92583a5-41b2-488f-84b2-9655b1f78200"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"RepeatedTiming", "[", 
  RowBox[{"(", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"res", "=", 
     RowBox[{"Table", "[", 
      RowBox[{"Null", ",", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"i", ",", 
         RowBox[{"10", "^", "5"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], ";", 
    "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"Do", "[", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"res", "[", 
        RowBox[{"[", "i", "]"}], "]"}], "=", 
       RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
        RowBox[{"pts", "[", 
         RowBox[{"[", "i", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
      
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"i", ",", "1", ",", 
        RowBox[{"10", "^", "5"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}], ";", 
    "\[IndentingNewLine]", "res", ";"}], ")"}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[239]:=",ExpressionUUID->"7d42a4ad-d8b7-47da-8f36-c203c74425c4"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"9.781249`", ",", "Null"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[239]=",ExpressionUUID->"8067052e-7ad4-458a-a100-652a2b6b6ccb"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Try a more \"Wolfram way\" of doing this by using ",
 ButtonBox["Table",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Table.html"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Table.html"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"59d6c6a6-137e-427c-8110-18a4460a9c0d"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"RepeatedTiming", "[", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"res", "=", 
    RowBox[{"Table", "[", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Sin", "[", 
       RowBox[{"pts", "[", 
        RowBox[{"[", "i", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"i", ",", "1", ",", 
        RowBox[{"10", "^", "5"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[243]:=",ExpressionUUID->"297278d1-0de6-4732-95e0-ef155efff4bf"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0.009836515625`", ",", "Null"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[243]=",ExpressionUUID->"7fb10ec4-91ff-4ef8-8b98-11a154fe5237"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["This is about a thousand times faster.", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9a23c4b0-7e7c-48a4-84f4-7631dc78c7e5"],

Cell["Go further down the functional line by using Map:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fb6d7775-cc5a-4f42-8c1d-c805384149f3"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"RepeatedTiming", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"res", "=", 
    RowBox[{"Sin", "/@", "pts"}]}], ";"}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[244]:=",ExpressionUUID->"33583319-3e83-4106-866c-b8596109c88f"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0.0096563125`", ",", "Null"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[244]=",ExpressionUUID->"24cbf39e-d52b-4de5-937e-26cd999c02d7"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["In this case, Map and Table have equivalent speeds.", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c88b2168-b465-412a-ae20-b3e070dcfbc6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Finally, note that ",
 ButtonBox["Sin",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Sin.html"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Sin.html"],
 " has the attribute ",
 ButtonBox["Listable",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Listable.html"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Listable.html"],
 ":"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a79ff00e-34db-4086-9e8b-64a0f7ed1c11"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Attributes", "[", "Sin", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[227]:=",ExpressionUUID->"71422b5f-591d-444f-b8fc-95b24c1fba36"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"Listable", ",", "NumericFunction", ",", "Protected"}], 
  "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[227]=",ExpressionUUID->"932fa7b8-5021-4c59-9a0a-d7ee98e04f9f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["This means that it works on lists automatically:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1aa80d89-67e5-4130-8936-55746b7fe074"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"RepeatedTiming", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"res", "=", 
    RowBox[{"Sin", "[", "pts", "]"}]}], ";"}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[241]:=",ExpressionUUID->"56a425c0-2fe1-4207-ae4c-ff81a99c2756"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"0.00005468157958984375`", ",", "Null"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[241]=",ExpressionUUID->"96673182-153b-4190-9af1-dd2d394f2305"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
This is far and away the fastest option, and in particular it is about \
200,000 times faster than the naive procedural approach. It pays off not only \
to use built-in functions, but to be aware of their special attributes and \
extended capabilities.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c04afb9f-d6c7-4474-bf20-1747f08790a1"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Overload Functions", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"a2d22cd1-2316-4a84-8416-5e9052c2710f"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"function1", "[", "list_List", "]"}], ":=", 
  RowBox[{"If", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Length", "[", "list", "]"}], "===", "0"}], ",", "0", ",", 
    RowBox[{"1", "/", 
     RowBox[{"Length", "[", "list", "]"}]}]}], "]"}]}]], "Input",ExpressionUUI\
D->"b72c3011-abcd-4ba1-acb8-0c8315c58746"],

Cell["Can be replaced with:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b5015a5e-44bb-4d18-8ab2-e3c1944aa8dd"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"function2", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", "}"}], "]"}], ":=", "0"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"function2", "[", "list_List", "]"}], ":=", 
  RowBox[{"1", "/", 
   RowBox[{"Length", "[", "list", "]"}]}]}]}], "Input",ExpressionUUID->\
"3dc5caa1-22e6-4ac0-acfe-9015d10c5665"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"RepeatedTiming", "[", 
  RowBox[{"function1", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", "}"}], "]"}], "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"RepeatedTiming", "[", 
  RowBox[{"function2", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", "}"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->
  "In[264]:=",ExpressionUUID->"08544c69-4c8e-4ce1-9125-a80a34d8c65e"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"2.681494140625`3.*^-6", ",", "0"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[264]=",ExpressionUUID->"5cc6b5d6-7274-4494-b0cf-3a85b7891cde"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{"3.424479166667`1.*^-7", ",", "0"}], "}"}]], "Output",
 CellLabel->
  "Out[265]=",ExpressionUUID->"a25e35ab-0c2d-4cdf-9a93-5352278939cc"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Overloading function definitions reduces function sizes and makes them \
easier to read. Keeping track of what branch of an ",
 ButtonBox["If",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/If.html"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/If.html"],
 " statement you are in takes more effort than locating ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"nameOfMyFunction", "[", "caseThatIAmInterestedIn", "]"}]], "Input",
  ExpressionUUID->"38c1701c-c3d8-4785-b357-bff591e7b7e5"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5c22f6ea-66aa-4be0-9cce-552991c9885f"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Compile", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"2fce3089-76ee-49c1-abf9-6f1809956f85"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The ",
 ButtonBox["Compile",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Compile.html"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/Compile.html"],
 " function takes Wolfram Language code and allows you to pre-declare the \
types (real, complex, etc.) and structures (value, list, matrix, etc.) of \
input arguments. Not everything can be compiled\[LongDash]and very simple \
code might not benefit\[LongDash]but complex low-level numerical code can \
experience a dramatic speedup. Furthermore, if your code is compilable, then \
you can also use the option ",
 ButtonBox["CompilationTarget",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/CompilationTarget.html"], 
    None},
  ButtonNote->
   "https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/CompilationTarget.html"],
 "\[Rule]\"C\" to generate C code, call your C compiler to compile it to a \
DLL and link the DLL back into Mathematica\[LongDash]all automatically."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"20f4c0ae-5b2f-4f00-bb7e-2e8b30165efe"],

Cell["\<\
There is more overhead in the compilation stage, but the DLL runs directly on \
your CPU, not on the Mathematica virtual machine, so the results can be even \
faster:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b0cc0c5d-2abd-4584-a68d-70fedf183474"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"arg", "=", 
   RowBox[{"Range", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"-", "50."}], ",", "50.", ",", "0.25"}], "]"}]}], ";"}]], "Input",\

 CellLabel->
  "In[159]:=",ExpressionUUID->"570d8902-2504-4a08-b86f-eb13dc972915"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"fn", "=", 
   RowBox[{"Function", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", "x", "}"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"Block", "[", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"sum", "=", "1.0"}], ",", 
         RowBox[{"inc", "=", "1.0"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"Do", "[", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"inc", "*=", 
            RowBox[{"x", "/", "i"}]}], ";", 
           RowBox[{"sum", "+=", "inc"}]}], ",", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
           RowBox[{"i", ",", "10000"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], ";", "sum"}]}], 
      "]"}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->
